<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56be31c5-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s2163"><num value="2163">§ 2163.</num><heading> Removal of officer from active duty; action by Secretary</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may remove an officer from active duty if his removal is recommended by a board of inquiry under <ref href="/us/usc/t14/s2159">section 2159 of this title</ref>. The Secretary’s action in such as case is final and conclusive.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56be31c6-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/88/130/s1/10/C">Pub. L. 88–130, § 1(10)(C)</ref>, <date date="1963-09-24">Sept. 24, 1963</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/77/189">77 Stat. 189</ref>, § 326; renumbered § 2163 and amended <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI">Pub. L. 115–282, title I</ref>, §§ 112(b), 123(b)(2), <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4216">132 Stat. 4216</ref>, 4240; <ref href="/us/pl/119/60/dG/tLXXII/s7223/d/1/B">Pub. L. 119–60, div. G, title LXXII, § 7223(d)(1)(B)</ref>, <date date="2025-12-18">Dec. 18, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/1702">139 Stat. 1702</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
